    "refcode_long": "Counsels on Sabbath School Work, p. 125.2 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Do not allow all your strength and energy to be given to worldly, temporal things during the week, and so have no energy and moral strength to give to the service of Christ on the Sabbath. There is earnest work to be done just now. We have not a moment&apos;s time to use selfishly. Let all we do be done with an eye single to the glory of God. Never rest till every child in your class is brought to the saving knowledge of Christ.&mdash;<span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"TSS 14.1\" data-link=\"121.44\"><em>Testimonies on Sabbath-School Work</em>, 14</span>.",
